# Cloudflare Pages routing
#
# Pretty blog URLs: /blog/posts/{slug} should serve /blog/post.html
# content while keeping the slug in the URL bar.
#
# IMPORTANT: the destination is `/blog/post` (no .html). CF Pages
# auto-strips `.html` from any URL it serves directly — if we used
# `/blog/post.html` here, the auto-strip would turn this rewrite into
# a 308 redirect to `/blog/post`, dropping the slug. Using the
# extensionless form means CF Pages internally resolves `/blog/post`
# to `/blog/post.html` without changing the URL.

/blog/posts/*   /blog/post   200
/blog/posts/*/  /blog/post   200
